result.name: Chopsticks Fork n Knife

reviews.text: Nice staff and helpful, but food are mediocre at most.  Eel was not fresh, and rice are not properly cooked. Overly price indeed

Just being here for a working lunch, generally speaking, quite a fancy place. The menu offers a full array of international dishes ranging from Mexico to Chinese, and Thailand curries. I ordered a nori-rice rolls with veggies, corn chip with avocado sauce.

Do NOT get the tonkatsu bento. For 118hkd, you get the cutlet on a huge bed of raw cabbage, lots of rice, but a thimble of mayonnaise... No other sauce in sight. At least the regular coffee is decent.
One of the worst food I've had. The korean beef bulgogi rice is extremely oily and sweet, priced at $108+10% which is ridiculous. And the waffles are hard as stone.
Very quiet on that Sunday evening and we were the only customer. Our ordered black truffle risotto and Thai green curry duck rice were very hot and tasty. The prices were reasonable.
